%N A083087 Square table read by antidiagonals which forms a permutation of the natural numbers: T(n,0) = floor(n*x/(x-1))+1, T(n,k+1) = ceiling(x*T(n,k)), for n>=0, k>=0, where x = 1 + sqrt(2).
%C A083087 The array in A083087 is the dispersion of the sequence given floor(n+1+n*sqrt(2)). The Mathematica program at A191438 generates A083087 using f[n_]:=Floor[n*x+n+1] instead of f[n_]:=Floor[n*x+n]. - _Clark Kimberling_, Jun 04 2011
%F A083087 T(n,k+1) = 2*T(n,k) + T(n,k-1) + 1 for n>=0, k>=1.
